ZCZC GE03
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
DURING FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY HIGH PRESSURE WILL LIE ACROSS SERN BRITAIN
FRANCE AND BISCAY WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING NWARDS ACROSS IRELAND AND TO THE
W OF ICELAND.
A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 976 LYING TO THE E OF ICELAND AT FIRST WILL
MOV STEADILY S-EWARDS TO SERN SCANDINAVIA. DURING SATURDAY THE RIDGE AXIS
WILL MOV INTO THE N SEA AS PRESSURE FALLS FM THE W. A TRANSITORY LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE WILL MOV S-EWARDS ACROSS THE UK ON MONDAY AND INTO THE LOW COUNTRIES
WITH HIGH PRESSURE OVER IBERIA AND ICELAND. W OR NW WINDS WILL BE STRG IN
THE SERN N SEA ON FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY MORNING WITH GALES FURTHER
N AND POSS SEV GALES DURING SATURDAY IN VIKING N AND S UTSIRE FORTIES
FISHERN AND FAIR ISLE. GALES MAY DEVELOP IN GERMAN BIGHT AND HUMBER LATER
SATURDAY. WINDS WILL GRADUALLY DECREASE TO OCNL STRG ON SUNDAY AND CONTINUING
OCNL STRG ON MONDAY
